---
import DocLayout from "../../layouts/DocLayout.astro";
---

<DocLayout
    title="Artist Guide"
    description="How to create themes, compose music, and earn royalties on Hearth."
    breadcrumb="Artists"
    emoji="ðŸŽ¨"
>
    <div class="intro">
        <p>
            Hearth is waiting for your art. We are creating a marketplace for 3D
            environments, character skins, and audio tracks. Contribute to the
            "Hallmark 2.0" ecosystem and earn perpetual royalties.
        </p>
    </div>

    <h2>1. Contributing Themes</h2>
    <p>
        A Theme in Hearth is more than just a background image. It controls the
        entire atmosphere: fog, lighting, ground textures, and particle systems.
    </p>

    <div class="glass-panel p-6 my-8 border border-white/10 rounded-xl">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-accent mb-4">Theme Spec (v1.0)</h3>
        <pre
            class="bg-black/40 p-4 rounded-lg text-xs font-mono text-white/80 overflow-x-auto border border-white/10">
interface SceneTheme &#123;
    label: string;          // e.g. "Cyberpunk City"
    fogColor: number;       // Hex color for distance fog
    fogDensity: number;     // 0.01 to 0.1
    groundColor: number;    // Base color of the infinite plane
    ambientColor: number;   // Global illumination tint
    tone: 'warm' | 'cool' | 'mystical' | 'solemn';
&#125;
    </pre>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-white/70">
            To submit a theme, create a Pull Request with your theme definition
            in <code>src/lib/config.ts</code>
            and include 3 high-quality screenshots.
        </p>
    </div>

    <h2>2. 3D Assets (GLB)</h2>
    <p>We support standard glTF 2.0 binary files (`.glb`) for scene props.</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 mt-4 text-white/70">
        <li>
            <strong>Poly Count</strong>: Keep individual props under 5,000 tris.
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Textures</strong>: Max 1024x1024. Use compressed KTX2 if
            possible.
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Animations</strong>: Bake animations into the GLB. Loopable
            idle animations are preferred.
        </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Audio Tracks</h2>
    <p>
        Music is the emotional core of Hearth. We accept original compositions
        in the following categories:
    </p>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 my-6">
        <div class="p-4 border border-white/10 rounded-lg bg-white/5">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-white mb-2">Piano / Classical</h4>
            <p class="text-xs text-white/50">Romantic, timeless, acoustic.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 border border-white/10 rounded-lg bg-white/5">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-white mb-2">Lo-Fi / Ambient</h4>
            <p class="text-xs text-white/50">Relaxing, modern, nostalgic.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 border border-white/10 rounded-lg bg-white/5">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-white mb-2">Cinematic</h4>
            <p class="text-xs text-white/50">Epic, swelling, emotional.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 border border-white/10 rounded-lg bg-white/5">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-white mb-2">Nature / SFX</h4>
            <p class="text-xs text-white/50">Rain, forest, ocean sounds.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <h2>4. Royalty Model</h2>
    <p>
        When the NFT marketplace launches (Phase 3), artists will receive a <strong
            >30% direct revenue share</strong
        >
        on mints using their assets.
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Smart contracts handle automatic payouts.</li>
        <li>
            Artists retain IP rights; Hearth gets a non-exclusive perpetual
            license.
        </li>
        <li>Top-tier artists get "Featured" placement in the Composer UI.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Critique & Quality Assurance</h2>
    <p>
        We aim for <strong>"Pixar-lite"</strong> quality.
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>
            <strong>Cohesion</strong>: Assets must look good together. Avoid
            mixing low-poly with photoreal.
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Optimized</strong>: Assets must load fast on mobile (under
            2MB total scene).
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Accessibility</strong>: Colors must have sufficient
            contrast. Audio shouldn't be jarring.
        </li>
    </ul>
</DocLayout>

